Questions:
Express with the aid of an integral the area bounded by the following curves:
(1) the coordinate axes, the straight line x=3 and the parabola y=x²+1;
(2) the axis of abscissae, the straight lines x=a, x=b and the curve y=eˣ+2 (b>a);
(3) the axis of abscissae and the arc of the sine wave y=sin x corresponding to the first half-period;
(4) the parabolas y=x² and y=8-x²;
(5) the parabolas y=x² and y=√x;
(6) the curves y=ln x and y=ln²x.

Use the formula obtained in the previous example to evaluate the integrals:
(1)∫[0 to 10] x dx; (2)∫[a-2 to a+2] dx; (3)∫[a/2 to a] x²dx; (4)∫[a to 2a] b²x²dx;
(5)∫[0 to m](3x²-x+1)dx; (6)∫[0 to m](x²+m²)/m² dx;
(7)∫[1 to 2.5](2x+1)²dx; (8)∫[a to b](x-a)(x-b)dx

Answers:
(1) [x²/2] from 0 to 10 = 50; (2) [x] from a-2 to a+2 = 4;
(3) [x³/3] from a/2 to a = 7a³/24; (4) b²[x³/3] from a to 2a = 7a³b²/3;
(5) [x³-x²/2+x] from 0 to m = m³-m²/2+m; (6) (1/m²)[x³/3+m²x] from 0 to m = 4m/3;
(7) ∫(4x²+4x+1)dx = [4x³/3+2x²+x] from 1 to 2.5 = 31.5;
(8) ∫(x²-(a+b)x+ab)dx = (b-a)³(a+b)/2 - ab(b-a) = -(b-a)³/6.

